id: pm-web-5myg
title: "Daily Release fails at changelog:check: generate step uses prepend/since-previous-tag but check expects replace/all-release-tags"
description: "Run 27430061038 (first ever pm-web release run to actually execute, after the ubuntu-latest runner fix) failed: the workflow's generate step ran 'npm run changelog -- --github-step-summary' (mode prepend, --since-previous-tag --until-release-tag) while 'npm run changelog:check' validates with mode replace + --all-release-tags. The two layouts can never agree once the version is bumped, so changelog:check always exits 1 and the release aborts before commit/tag/publish. Siblings (pm-todos et al.) regenerate with replace/all-release-tags in the release workflow. Fix: call 'npm run changelog:full -- --github-step-summary' (already the exact replace/all-release-tags counterpart of changelog:check) in release.yml."
type: Task
status: in_progress
priority: 1
tags[3]: changelog,ci,release-automation
created_at: "2026-06-12T22:35:38.797Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-12T22:35:39.167Z"
author: codex
acceptance_criteria: Dispatched Daily Release run completes successfully end-to-end and publishes pm-web to npm + GitHub release
files[1]{path,scope,note}:
  .github/workflows/release.yml,project,"changelog -> changelog:full in the generate step"
body: ""
